{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance |nativename = وزارت فرهنگ و ارشاد اسلامی |nativename_a = |nativename_r = |logo = Coat of arms of Iran.svg |logo_width = 100px |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |formed = 18 August 1984 |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = |superseding = |jurisdiction = [[Islamic Republic of Iran]] |headquarters = |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = |minister1_pfo = |minister2_name = |minister2_pfo = |chief1_name = [[Abbas Salehi]] |chief1_position = |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = [http://www.farhang.gov.ir/ Official Website] |footnotes = }} {{Politics of Iran}}
The '''Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance''' ({{lang-fa|وزارت فرهنگ و ارشاد اسلامی}} also known as '''Ershad''' {{lang|fa|ارشاد}}) is the [[ministry of Culture]] of the [[Islamic Republic of Iran]]. It is responsible for [[censorship|restricting access]] to any media that violates Islamic ethics or promotes values alien to the [[Iranian Revolution]].<ref>[https://www.farhang.gov.ir/en/profileofministry/responsibilities Official website o the Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance]</ref> It was formed after the Revolution by merger of the Ministry of Culture and Art and the Ministry of Information and Tourism.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20080803173726/http://www.iranculture.org/en/nahad/ershad.php Responsibilities and organizational structure of Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance]</ref>
For the importation and exportation of motion picture, cinematographic and television films, audio tapes, phonographic discs, books and other publications, brochures, pamphlets, commercial advertisement products, business catalogues, pictures, gravures, paintings, tableaux, etc., licenses are required to be obtained from the Ministry of Culture and Islamic Guidance.<ref>[http://www.irantradelaw.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Irans-Foreign-Trade-Regime-Report.pdf Foreign Trade Regime of the IRI] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130310232210/http://www.irantradelaw.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Irans-Foreign-Trade-Regime-Report.pdf |date=2013-03-10 }} Memorandum</ref> In addition, the ministry is one of the governmental bodies that are responsible for exporting the Islamic revolution<ref name=bar09>{{cite journal|last=Bar|first=Shmuel|title=Iranian terrorist policy and "export of revolution"|journal=Interdisciplinary Center|year=2009|url=http://www.herzliyaconference.org/_Uploads/2903Iranian.pdf|accessdate=28 July 2013}}</ref> and one of the three "sovereign" ministerial bodies of Iran due to nature of its work at home and abroad.<ref>{{cite news|last=al Labbad|first=Mustafa|title=Rouhani’s Cabinet Seeks New Balance in Iranian Policies|url=http://assafir.com/MulhakArticle.aspx?EditionId=2539&MulhakArticleId=1787820&MulhakId=6367#.Ug3dQ2TAVgs|accessdate=16 August 2013|newspaper=As Safir|date=15 August 2013}}</ref>
